WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:10.040 --> 00:00:12.920
Each year new stars emerge
on the gymnastics scene.

00:00:13.640 --> 00:00:16.400
We started to get to know
the talent on the road to Rio

00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:19.400
but a handful are already
preparing to shine in Tokyo.

00:00:19.480 --> 00:00:23.520
Here's a selection on 11-year-old rising
gymnasts from across the country.

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:26.080
Let's meet your future ones to watch.

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:36.760
First up is Megan Splain who trains
at Sapphire gymnastics club

00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:38.280
under the watchful eye of Steve Price,

00:00:38.360 --> 00:00:41.520
coach of 2013 Senior British
champion Gabby Jupp

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:44.600
and Australian youth Olympic
champion Teal Grindle.

00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:47.000
With a bright and bubbly personality,

00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:49.320
this young star certainly
knows how to perform.

00:00:49.400 --> 00:00:52.520
With fantastic potential
on the floor and all around

00:00:52.600 --> 00:00:55.280
she looks set to follow
in her teammate's footsteps.

00:00:56.360 --> 00:00:59.960
You can be sure to always see
her smiling - so watch this space!

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:08.000
Elegance and beauty.

00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:13.520
Emily Gibson from Europa is an
extremely strong beam and floor worker.

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:17.920
A gymnast, of former GB International
Rochelle Douglas

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:20.000
who trains Espoir champions

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:21.800
Catherine Lyons
and Georgia-MaeFenton.

00:01:21.880 --> 00:01:25.520
Emily performs difficult combinations
on the beam with expressive dance.

00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:29.360
A talented young gymnast
who's sure to impress.

00:01:33.160 --> 00:01:36.120
Next is one determined young gymnast
from South Durham,

00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:37.400
Courtney Burton.

00:01:39.560 --> 00:01:43.200
Courtney is calm and collected
across all four pieces of apparatus.

00:01:48.480 --> 00:01:50.920
She's a powerful gymnast
with a bright future.

00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:55.800
This pink lady has come a long way
and shows no signs of stopping.

00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:01.400
Next say hello to the city
of Manchesters' Ellie Cheetham.

00:02:02.720 --> 00:02:04.960
A flexible yet dynamic gymnast

00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:06.960
she is always focused
on the task ahead.

00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:11.200
Not only does she
swing well on the bars,

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:15.560
but executes powerful tumbles alongside
a crowd-pleasing performance.

00:02:18.760 --> 00:02:20.520
Manchester has a new star.

00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:26.560
Jolie Ruckley from Cardiff Olympic

00:02:26.640 --> 00:02:29.600
is a gymnast with heaps of energy
that is constantly improving.

00:02:32.840 --> 00:02:34.080
Precision is her strength

00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:36.320
making her a reliable
all-around-gymnast

00:02:36.400 --> 00:02:37.840
and a strong contender.

00:02:39.920 --> 00:02:43.480
Quietly confident,
Jolie is one of Wales' finest.

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:51.200
Meet Notts Laura Kaletha.

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:56.120
Small in size but big on power.

00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:58.040
Laura's speed and focus

00:02:58.120 --> 00:03:00.720
will ensure she has
an enviable skill set in the future.

00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:08.920
This little superstar has nerves of steel
and bags of potential.

00:03:16.760 --> 00:03:20.240
Our final one to watch is 11-year-old
power house, Taeja James

00:03:20.320 --> 00:03:21.600
from the city of Birmingham.

00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:24.400
A confident and stylish gymnast

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:26.680
who moves through
difficult skills with ease.

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:29.520
With an already established
set of unique skills

00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:32.640
this fierce gymnast will make sure
she has your attention.

00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:41.400
So we've seen only a small handful
of talent in this age group

00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:43.280
but it's clear the British women
are going to be

00:03:43.360 --> 00:03:45.520
a force to be reckoned with
for years to come.

00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:51.960
You heard it here first,
remember their names.

